title: For Sale:  Some of you need to read NFA rules and regs.....please read this post
postcontent:
Fellow traders.  I am seeing a few postings with SBR AR uppers meaning under 16", I then click your other items for sale and you have a standard AR complete rifle for sale.

Did you know that if you own an AR with a barrel 16" or longer and have the SBR upper in you possession that you are in violation of the NFA and could suffer serious legal consequences unless you possess a federal tax stamp for the SBR.  If you do not own an AR lower and own that SBR upper you are ok, but the day you acquire the lower without the stamp you are violating federal laws.

Reason being is that if you own both it takes no effort to switch out the uppers and then have an unlicensed SBR.

Believe it or not some federal agents aren't out to get everyone and I hope you all read this posting and then read the laws.
